---
import { SITE } from '~/config.mjs';
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Resume from '../assets/pdfs/Januston_Nicholas_Resume_2023.pdf'
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Features2 from '~/components/widgets/Features2.astro';
import Steps from '~/components/widgets/Steps.astro';
import Content from '~/components/widgets/Content.astro';
import LatestPosts from '~/components/blog/LatestPosts.astro';
import FAQs from '~/components/widgets/FAQs.astro';
import CallToAction from '~/components/widgets/CallToAction.astro';
import Features from '~/components/widgets/Features.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon';
const meta = {
  title: SITE.title,
  description: SITE.description,
  dontUseTitleTemplate: true,
};
---

<Layout {meta}>
  <!-- Hero Widget ******************* -->

  <Hero>
    <Fragment slot="title">
      Hi, I'm <span class="text-accent dark:text-white highlight"> Januston Nicholas</span>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <span class="sm:inline">
        <span class="font-semibold">As a passionate web and software developer 🌐 with extensive experience, I bring a wealth of knowledge and expertise to every project. 💻</span> 
        <span class="font-semibold">I love to create innovative solutions that make a real difference in people's lives. 🔥</span>
        </br></br>
        <span class="font-semibold">When I'm not coding, you can usually find me relaxing by playing video games, reading, or watching my favorite shows. 🎮📚📺</span>
        <span class="font-semibold">If you're looking for a dedicated and talented developer to bring your ideas to life, I'm here to help. Let's create something amazing together! 🤝💪🚀</span> 
        </br></br>
        <span>
          <a class="btn" href={Resume} target="_blank">Resume</a>
        </span>
    </Fragment>
  </Hero>

  <!-- Content Widget **************** -->
  <Content
    isReversed
    image={{
      src: import('~/assets/images/appficiency.png'),
      alt: 'Colorful Image',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">Appficiency</h3>
      During my tenure at Appficiency, a proud recipient of NetSuite’s distinguished Alliance Partner Spotlight Award for both Construction and Professional Sports, I played an instrumental role in the SST team as a Software Developer Co-op. 🔧 Immersing myself in the NetSuite environment, I meticulously crafted solutions, wrote scripts using SuiteScript 2.x, and pioneered automation processes that negated the need for manual content creation in NetSuite. These innovations not only streamlined operations but also significantly elevated the efficacy and user experience of our solutions. 🛠️
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
    highlight="Here are some of the places where I've worked"
    title="Software Development Experience"
    image={{
      src: import('~/assets/images/yuja.jpg'),
      alt: 'Colorful Image',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">YuJa</h3>
      During my time at Yuja as a Full Stack Developer, I worked on several projects that improved the functionality and usability of the company's products. 🚀 I developed API endpoints to allow seamless integration of the company's Chrome extension with other tools, and created authentication workflows for Learning Management Systems (LMS), streamlining the quiz creation process and saving significant time for instructors. 🔑
      <br/><br/>
      As part of my role, I also redesigned a key feature of the platform using React and updated quiz interception code for multiple learning management systems, ensuring accurate assessment of student performance and improving quiz-taking integrity. 🎓 I have experience working with LTI, LMS, Chrome Extensions, React, TypeScript, HTML, CSS, SQL, Figma, and Github. 💻  
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
    isReversed
    image={{
      src: import('~/assets/images/ss&c.jpg'),
      alt: 'Colorful Image',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">SS&C Technologies</h3>
      During my time at SS&C Technologies as a Software Developer, I spearheaded several projects that significantly improved the efficiency and user experience of the company's systems. 🔧 Utilizing a variety of tools and technologies, including Apache Nifi, Five9, PostgreSQL, Java, Spring Boot, HTML, CSS, and Github, I developed an API that streamlined deletion of outdated records in an Inference Datastore and an HTML Tree 🌳 to display business groups using API calls, resulting in better navigation for users. Additionally, I optimized Five9 call flows and reorganized Five9 data, reducing caller wait times and improving overall caller experience. 📞  
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
  image={{
    src: import('~/assets/images/purolator.jpg'),
    alt: 'Colorful Image',
  }}>
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">Purolator</h3>
      During my time as a Marketing Front End Developer at Purolator 🚚, I contributed to several projects that improved the company's online presence and user experience. One of my notable accomplishments was revamping the Purolator website using Drupal 8, PHP, HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, resulting in a measurable increase in website traffic 💻. Additionally, I developed an innovative HTML and JSON generator using a PHP script and template, which dynamically produced over 700 locator pages through the use of API calls and CSV data 💾. This project significantly improved the user experience and increased overall customer satisfaction 🌎. My proficiency in Drupal 8, PHP, HTML, CSS, Javascript, and Photoshop allowed me to effectively contribute to these projects.
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
    isReversed
    image={{
      src: import('~/assets/images/teranet.jpg'),
      alt: 'Colorful Image',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">Teranet</h3>
      During my time at Teranet 🏞️ as a Software Developer, I played an integral role in the development of the client portal, utilizing Java, Angular JS, JavaScript, HTML, and Python to significantly enhance the user experience. Notable achievements include the successful implementation of intuitive and user-friendly features, resulting in increased engagement and higher user satisfaction levels. 📈
      <br/><br/>
      I also used Postman, SQL Developer, and Soap UI 📨💾🧼 to streamline debugging and updating of consumer reports through data retrieval and API requests. In my role, I worked with Apache Tomcat 🐈, HTML, CSS, Angular JS, Batch Script Automation, Python with ImageMagick, SQL, and Github to successfully complete these projects.
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
  image={{
    src: import('~/assets/images/tyltgo.jpg'),
    alt: 'Colorful Image',
  }}>
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">TyltGo (YCS20)</h3>
      As a Web Developer at TyltGo (YCS20), I collaborated with a cross-functional team to redesign and add features to a website using Angular 2+, HTML, Sass, CSS, and Typescript. This resulted in increased traffic 📈 and user engagement 👥.
      <br/><br/>
      💻 I led the development of a new client portal and implemented Jasmine and Karma test cases, reducing overall development time. I also used Figma 🎨 and Bootstrap to design and style the website.
      <br/><br/>
      In addition to my technical expertise in Angular 2+, HTML, CSS, Typescript, Sass, Figma, and Bootstrap, I gained experience working in an agile development 🏃‍♂️ environment and honed my collaboration and communication skills.
    </Fragment>
  </Content>
  <!-- Features2 Widget ************** -->

  <Features2
    title="Personal and University Projects"
    subtitle=""
    highlight="Here are some recent projects that I have been involved in"
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Personal Website 🌐',
        description:
          "👋 Welcome to my personal website, and I'm thrilled you found it! This website is a fun way for me to showcase my experiences and skills as a web developer. It was built using a range of technologies, including HTML, CSS/SASS, and Javascript. I also utilized the powerful open-source Astro 2.0 framework and the versatile Tailwind CSS library 🌀 to create a seamless and modern design. Thank you for taking the time to explore my website and learn more about my work! ",
        icon: 'tabler:app-window',
      },
      {
        title: 'Real-Time OS 🕰️',
        description:
          "Check out my experience working on a real-time operating system project! I collaborated with a team to develop the system using the μVision Kiel IDE and implemented a binary buddy system to manage memory. We achieved interprocess communication with mailboxes and prioritized tasks using an Earliest Deadline First (EDF) scheduling algorithm to ensure timely completion ⏰. It was a challenging and rewarding project, and I'm proud to have been a part of it!",
        icon: 'tabler:cpu',
      },
      {
        title: 'MLB Hall of Fame Predictor ⚾️',
        description:
          "Introducing the MLB Hall of Fame Predictor! Using the powerful SK-Learn library in Python 🐍, I've created a predictive model that determines a player's likelihood of being inducted into the Hall of Fame based on their stats. With the help of SQL, I ensured that the baseball data bank from 2022 was properly scrubbed and outputted to a CSV for model training and testing. The accuracy of the model is a stunning 94%, so get ready to predict the future Hall of Famers! 🏆⚾️",
        icon: 'tabler:brand-python',
      },
      {
        title: 'Taiga Bot 🤖',
        description:
          "Meet the Taiga bot, a Discord bot I developed in early 2021! With Discord's ban on public music bots, I saw a need for a new solution. Taiga not only plays music through Discord 🎵, but it also finds gifs and images based on prompts. This versatile bot can join and leave voice channels, queue up music, loop queues or songs, and even pause music. I used JavaScript and Node.js with the Slappey JS library to bring this project to life. The Taiga bot has been a great addition to my Discord server, providing my friends and me with endless entertainment during our calls 📞.",
        icon: 'tabler:brand-discord',
      },
      {
        title: 'RGB Light Sign 💡',
        description:
          "I had the opportunity to work on an exciting hardware project where I designed and created a 36 by 2.5 inch RGB light board, which could be programmed and controlled using a PIC 16F690 microcontroller.  I even designed the PCB using the Eagle board development software 🦅 and hand-assembled and soldered each board myself. The programming was done in assembly language, and the final product had the ability to strobe and change colors with ease. The end result was a mesmerizing LED sign, which not only showcased my hardware skills but also my ability to design and program functional and visually appealing products.",
        icon: 'tabler:bulb',
      },
      {
        title: 'Line Tracing Robot 🔍',
        description:
          "As a computer engineering student 👨‍🔬, I also enjoy working on hardware projects. One of my earliest projects was the Line Tracing Robot, which was equipped with two UV sensors and controlled using the PIC 16F690 microcontroller. This bot was programmed in assembly language and could navigate custom tracks by detecting and following the reflected UV light with its sensors 🎚️. It was a challenging and exciting project that allowed me to gain hands-on experience with both hardware and software.",
        icon: 'tabler:crosshair',
      },
    ]}
  />

  <!-- CallToAction Widget *********** -->
  <Content
    highlight="Here's a quick look at the skills I have developed throughout my career"
    title="Technical Skills"
  >
    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Angular 2+</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Angular JS</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Astro</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Assembly</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Batch Scripts</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Bootstrap</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">C</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">C++</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Chrome Extension</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">CSS/Sass</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Docker</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Drupal 8</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Five9</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Git/GitHub</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">HTML5</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Java</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">JavaScript</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">LMS</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">LTI</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Material UI</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">MySQL</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Nifi</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">PHP</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">React</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">SQL Developer</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Typescript</div>
      <div class="chip mx-2 my-2">Visual Studio Code</div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Features
    title="Want to work with me?"
    items={[]}
  >
    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <a class="btn" href="mailto: januston.nicholas@outlook.com" target="_blank"><Icon name='tabler:mail' class="w-10 h-10 mr-3"/>Send me an email</a>
    </Fragment>
  </Features>
</Layout>
